seal     : The pipeline predicts one token. But ask the model to predict many tokens of working-out before its final answer — a chain of thought — and let it spend more compute at inference time, and its performance on hard problems jumps. This is the 2024–2025 frontier: reasoning not as a new faculty bolted on, but as the next-token engine, run at length and pointed at itself. The same prediction, iterated, becomes something that looks like thinking.
